eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 10 Years
Maximum age: 40 Years
Patients who are not practicing adequate contraception if the participants are of child bearing potential
Patients with septicemia or severe infection
Patients must not have a history of allergic reactions attributed to compounds of similar chemical or biologic composition to erlotinib
Patients must have measurable tumor size (2 cm^2) with an expected survival of >= 12 weeks
No  hemoptysis within the past 12 months (defined as bright red blood in sputum of > 1 teaspoon)

Patients who have previously received high dose therapy/autologous stem cell
             transplant are eligible
Patients with melanoma of mucosal or ocular primary
Any female that is trying to get pregnant

groups.description: Patients undergo IMRT QD five days a week for 6 weeks and receive concurrent cisplatin IV over 1-2 hours once weekly for 6 weeks.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Arm 1 (IMRT, cisplatin)

outcome_measures.measure: Incidence second of primary lung tumors

outcome_measures.analysis_method: The proportion of VHR T-ALL patients with EOC MRD >= 0.1% who become MRD negative (MRD undetectable) after the three high-risk BFM blocks of therapy, will be estimated. EFS for these patients (who continue on chemotherapy) will be compared with those who continue to have detectable MRD and who may receive other treatment options including hematopoietic stem cell transplant. Comparison will be descriptive.
outcome_measures.measure: EFS between very high risk (VHR) T-ALL patients treated with HR BFM intensification blocks who become MRD negative and those who remain MRD positive at the end of HR Block 3

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Compared for isolated CNS, isolated bone marrow, and combined bone marrow relapse between IR patients on the non-bortezomib containing arm on this study (no CRT) with similar patients on AALL0434 (+ CRT).
